Hourly pH

Chelsey Wegener

11/3/2020

Average hourly pH

Data at EOS are collected every 6 minutes, data at China Camp and Richardson Bay is collected every 15 minutes. No pH data available at Fort Point. I’m going to convert all data to average hourly (60min) salinity so that everything is consitent. The outliers were removed before this step. Outliers detected by QC flag and +/- 2sd from 7 day rolling mean. Using averageTime function in openair package to calculate hourly salinity mean. For timeAverage function to work, you need a date or POSIXct column named “date”. interval = frequency of data collection.

China Camp

cc<-read.csv("C:/Users/chels/Box Sync/Thesis/Data/Working data/Bouy data/cc_ph_clean.csv", header = TRUE, sep=",", fileEncoding="UTF-8-BOM", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

cc<-subset(cc, select=c(DateTimeStamp, pH))

names(cc)[names(cc) == "DateTimeStamp"] <- "date"

cc$date<-as.POSIXct(cc$date, format = c("%m/%d/%Y %H:%M"))


cc_h_ph<- timeAverage(cc,
            avg.time="1 hour",
            data.thresh = 0,
            statistic = "mean",
            interval = "15 min",
            remove.calm = FALSE,
            type = "default")
## Warning: Missing dates detected, removing 12 lines
## Warning in checkPrep(mydata, vars, type = "default", remove.calm = FALSE, :
## Detected data with Daylight Saving Time, converting to UTC/GMT
cc_g<-cc_h_ph %>% ggplot(aes(x=date, y=pH, color=pH))+
  geom_point(alpha=0.5)+ylim(6.5,9)+
  labs(title="Hourly pH from China Camp",
       subtitle="01/01/2017 - 12/31/2019",
       caption= "data courtesy of NERR")

eos<-read.csv("C:/Users/chels/Box Sync/Thesis/Data/Working data/Bouy data/eos_ph_clean.csv", header = TRUE, sep=",", fileEncoding="UTF-8-BOM", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

names(eos)[names(eos) == "datetime"] <- "date"

eos$date<-as.POSIXct(eos$date, format = c("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ"))

            avg.time="1 hour",
